text: Emma Vasilyevna Gapchenko (; 24 February 1938 – 6 December 2021) was Russian archer. She won three gold medals at the world championships in 1969–73 and a bronze medal at the 1972 Summer Olympics. She died on 6 December 2021, at the age of 83. ==References== Category:1938 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Olympic bronze medalists for the Soviet Union Category:Archers
